, world, or global, in favor of a far less certain and much more open interpretive framework emphasizing the political.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aInternational relationsxPhilosophy. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : International Relations. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh1 aRosenau, James N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079149053240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791490532423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791490532/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles